    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="36"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Thayer, Charles/106: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 7, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. Your 265, December 26, 11 a.m. Charles W. Thayer, now at Kuibyshev, has been
                    designated Third Secretary and Vice Consul at Kabul to serve in a dual capacity.
                    The purpose of his assignment is to open the office at Kabul, and he has been
                    instructed to report to you for consultation en route.</p>
                <p>Please take appropriate steps to inform the Afghan Government of Thayer’s
                    assignment, stating that a much higher-ranking officer will be sent to Kabul to
                    take charge as soon as his transportation can be arranged.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
